{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://Vinnl.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"Amanda Coulson (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Amanda_Coulson\" title=\"Amanda Coulson\">Amanda Coulson</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> worked full-time as an emergency dispatcher during her career as an amateur boxer?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amanda_Coulson","retrieved":1778311516369},{"title":"one of the first studies of Indigenous Australian literature (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the author of <b><a href=\"/wiki/Black_Words,_White_Page\" title=\"Black Words, White Page\">one of the first studies of Indigenous Australian literature</a></b> only arrived in Australia as a doctoral student?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Words,_White_Page","retrieved":1778311516369},{"title":"a funerary inscription (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Claudia_Aster_inscription\" title=\"Claudia Aster inscription\">a funerary inscription</a></b> from <a href=\"/wiki/Campania\" title=\"Campania\">Campania</a> commemorates a Jerusalem-born woman, likely enslaved during the <a href=\"/wiki/First_Jewish%E2%80%93Roman_War\" title=\"First Jewish–Roman War\">First Jewish–Roman War</a>, who died at the age of 25?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Claudia_Aster_inscription","retrieved":1778311516373},{"title":"Fidel Sánchez Hernández (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Fidel_S%C3%A1nchez_Hern%C3%A1ndez\" title=\"Fidel Sánchez Hernández\">Fidel Sánchez Hernández</a></b>, the president of El Salvador, personally commanded troops during the 1969 <a href=\"/wiki/Football_War\" title=\"Football War\">Football War</a>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fidel_S%C3%A1nchez_Hern%C3%A1ndez","retrieved":1778311516374},{"title":"1935 Free City of Danzig parliamentary election (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the <b><a href=\"/wiki/1935_Free_City_of_Danzig_parliamentary_election\" title=\"1935 Free City of Danzig parliamentary election\">1935 Free City of Danzig parliamentary election</a></b> was seen as a setback for the <a href=\"/wiki/Nazi_Party\" title=\"Nazi Party\">Nazi Party</a>, even though it won an absolute majority of seats?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1935_Free_City_of_Danzig_parliamentary_election","retrieved":1778311516375},{"title":"Yasuko Agawa (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Yasuko_Agawa\" title=\"Yasuko Agawa\">Yasuko Agawa</a></b> was so sought after that she would sing at \"five different jazz clubs in a single night\"?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yasuko_Agawa","retrieved":1778311516376},{"title":"2024 League Two play-off final (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that Crawley Town F.C. reached the <b><a href=\"/wiki/2024_EFL_League_Two_play-off_final\" title=\"2024 EFL League Two play-off final\">2024 League Two play-off final</a></b> by winning their semi-final with an aggregate score of <span class=\"nowrap\">8–1</span>, the largest margin in <a href=\"/wiki/English_Football_League_play-offs\" title=\"English Football League play-offs\">EFL play-off</a> history?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2024_EFL_League_Two_play-off_final","retrieved":1778311516377},{"title":"deliberately avoided requesting delivery of the goods (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that a <a href=\"/wiki/Federal_government_of_Mexico\" title=\"Federal government of Mexico\">Mexican government</a> agency paid suppliers in full upfront, then <b><a href=\"/wiki/Segalmex_scandal\" title=\"Segalmex scandal\">deliberately avoided requesting delivery of the goods</a></b>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Segalmex_scandal","retrieved":1778311516382},{"title":"Ig Nobel Prize (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that winners of the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Ig_Nobel_Prize\" title=\"Ig Nobel Prize\">Ig Nobel Prize</a></b> are silenced 